= What do you love?
+ I like being able to have complete knowledge and understanding of a given
  system. As part of that I love when things are simple and unified.
+ As part of this, I love orchestration methods which allow large tasks to be
  broken into trival sub-parts for automation.
+ I like tangible describale things which is most common with hardware as it
  is perfectly verifiable and like taking black box items and ascribing
  function to it in #hai[AI] and third-party #hrf[communication] devices.
+ I always am interested in exapanding my horizons which is why I like reading
  and learning.
+ I like to creativly express myself through drawing and hardware do-dads.

= What are you good at?
+ I am decent at math and have good grasp of harder subjects like
  #hrf[functional analysis].
+ I like to search for good explainations for #hai[complex phenonum] which I
  think makes me better at understanding different things. I like to
  communicat that to other people through documentaton.
+ From both a usage a program side I have great knowledge of linux for
  #hrf[coding].

= What can you get paid for?
+ Weapons and survelance companys seem to be doing alright.
+ I have worked IT jobs in the past to get paid.
+ As the internet grows need for #hrf[better communications] increase
+ Most #hai[AI jobs] seem very boring but they pay well
+ People always need more computers, so IC design.

= What does the world need?
+ The world needs more organization tools to facilitate better
  #hrf[communication] between people as existing tools are currently dominated
  by algorithms.
+ The world needs more clairity in how our critical systems work. There are
  existing implementations of trivial functions that I want to improve on. I
  also want to creating tooling to #hai[understaning these AI] to promote
  simplicity.
+ There is a need for accountability and equity in this world but are more
  social than engineering problems.

